Zazu went missing during last February, and having been through multiple calls that did not yield results, Pachos received a call earlier this week that ended the streak of false hope. Finally back home, four-year-old Zazu bears some signs of struggle, but he is busy settling back in. ALSO READ: Noise complainants crank up the volume Pachos took him to the vet yesterday where he got some much-needed treatment to his beak, claws and wings, and also got a good dose of vitamins. She said she is just very relieved to have him back home after all this time. “My animals are like my children.” Read the full story in the next edition of Lowvelder.